        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-16T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-16T12:00:00-05:00" n="114"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d114">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/2643: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-16T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 16, 1918—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 17—10:48 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2366. My 2356, November 15. I received today memorandum from Swiss Minister<note
                        n="4" xml:id="d114fn4">
                        <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_191">p. 191</ref>.</note>
                    referring to conversation I had with him, see 2345 [<hi rend="italic"
                        >2356?</hi>],<note n="3" xml:id="d114fn3">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> and concerning question of uniting with
                    Switzerland Vorarlberg and Tyrol, which has been [discussed] in press. He
                    evidently wished to put in writing his position regarding matter, stating that
                    if Vorarlberg should ask to be united with Switzerland, the Federal Government
                    would examine seriously question, <pb facs="0275" n="187" xml:id="pg_187"/>
                    taking inspiration from President Wilson’s principles that Vorarlberg is
                    territory more united Switzerland than to Austria and at the present moment he
                    understands petition being circulated among population Vorarlberg in favor
                    incorporation into Switzerland Swiss Government, however, not yet approached on
                    matter. Swiss would not refuse to examine desires neighbor populations, though
                    has never expressed a wish of territorial expansion. He does not think question
                    uniting Tyrol to Switzerland will arise. This memorandum closes with reference
                    to fact that Switzerland, the small model society of nations, is happy to be
                    able to count on sympathy and comprehension of great American democracy, which
                    phrase, I think, refers to apprehended possibility that hereafter Italy might
                    ask Switzerland to return to her Italian Ticino Canton, taking Tyrol as
                    compensation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Page</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
